panTrapMibsModule.description: A MIB module containing definitions of managed objects implemented by specific Palo Alto Networks products.

panReceiveTime.name: panReceiveTime
panReceiveTime.description: Time the log was received at the management plane.

panSerial.name: panSerial
panSerial.description: Serial number of the device that generated the log.

panEventType.name: panEventType
panEventType.description: Specifies type of log; Values are traffic, threat, config, system and hip-match.

panEventSubType.name: panEventSubType
panEventSubType.description: Subtype of traffic log; Values are start, end, drop, and deny.

panHost.name: panHost
panHost.description: Host address of PAN device that generated the event.

panVsys.name: panVsys
panVsys.description: Virtual System associated with the session.

panSeqno.name: panSeqno
panSeqno.description: A 64-bit log entry identifier incremented sequentially. Each log type has a unique number space

panActionflags.name: panActionflags
panActionflags.description: A bit field indicating if the log was forwarded to Panorama.

panNatSource.name: panNatSource
panNatSource.description: If Source NAT performed, the post-NAT Source IP address.

panNatDestination.name: panNatDestination
panNatDestination.description: If Destination NAT performed, the post-NAT Destination IP address.

panRule.name: panRule
panRule.description: Name of the rule that the session matched.

panSrcUser.name: panSrcUser
panSrcUser.description: User name of the user that initiated the session.

panDstUser.name: panDstUser
panDstUser.description: User name of the user to which the session was destined.

panSourceZone.name: panSourceZone
panSourceZone.description: Zone the session was sourced from.

panDestinationZone.name: panDestinationZone
panDestinationZone.description: Zone the session was destined to.

panIngressInterface.name: panIngressInterface
panIngressInterface.description: Interface that the session was sourced form.

panEgressInterface.name: panEgressInterface
panEgressInterface.description: Interface that the session was destined to.

panLogForwardingProfile.name: panLogForwardingProfile
panLogForwardingProfile.description: Log Forwarding Profile that was applied to the session

panSessionID.name: panSessionID
panSessionID.description: An internal numerical identifier applied to each session.

panRepeatCount.name: panRepeatCount
panRepeatCount.description: Number of sessions with same Source IP, Destination IP, Application, and Subtype seen within 5 seconds; Used for ICMP only.

panSourcePort.name: panSourcePort
panSourcePort.description: Source port utilized by the session.

panDestinationPort.name: panDestinationPort
panDestinationPort.description: Destination port utilized by the session.

panFlags.name: panFlags
panFlags.description: 32 bit field that provides details on session.

panProtocol.name: panProtocol
panProtocol.description: IP protocol associated with the session

panAction.name: panAction
panAction.description: Action taken for the session; Values are allow or deny

panTimeGenerated.name: panTimeGenerated
panTimeGenerated.description: Time the log was generated on the data plane

panSrcloc.name: panSrcloc
panSrcloc.description: Source country or Internal region for private addresses. Maximum length is 32 bytes.

panDstloc.name: panDstloc
panDstloc.description: Destination country or Internal region for private addresses. Maximum length is 32 bytes.

panTrafficBytes.name: panTrafficBytes
panTrafficBytes.description: Number of total bytes (transmit and receive) for the session.

panTrafficPackets.name: panTrafficPackets
panTrafficPackets.description: Number of total packets (transmit and receive) for the session.

panTrafficCategory.name: panTrafficCategory
panTrafficCategory.description: URL category associated with the session (if applicable).

panConfigAdmin.name: panConfigAdmin
panConfigAdmin.description: Admin name who issued configuration command.

panThreatId.name: panThreatId
panThreatId.description: Palo Alto Networks identifier for the threat. It is a numerical identifier followed by a description in parenthesis for some Subtypes.

panThreatCategory.name: panThreatCategory
panThreatCategory.description: Provides URL Category for URL Subtype; For other subtypes the value is 'any'.

panThreatContentType.name: panThreatContentType
panThreatContentType.description: Content type of the HTTP response data. Maximum length 32 bytes. Applicable only when Subtype is URL.

panThreatSeverity.name: panThreatSeverity
panThreatSeverity.description: Severity associated with the threat; Values are informational, low, medium, high, critical.

panThreatDirection.name: panThreatDirection
panThreatDirection.description: Indicates the direction of the attack, 'client-to-server' or 'server-to-client'.

panMiscellaneous.name: panMiscellaneous
panMiscellaneous.description: The actual URI when the subtype is URL; File name or file type when the subtype is file; and File name when the subtype is virus.

panPcapId.name: panPcapId
panPcapId.description: A 64-bit unsigned integer denoting an ID that correlates threat pcaps with extended pcaps.

panFileDigest.name: panFileDigest
panFileDigest.description: A hash of the file that was sent to the Wildfire cloud.

panCloud.name: panCloud
panCloud.description: FQDN of the Wildfire cloud that analyzed the file.

panHipSourceUser.name: panHipSourceUser
panHipSourceUser.description: User name of the Source user.

panHipMatch.name: panHipMatch
panHipMatch.description: Name of the HIP Object or Profile.

panHipMatchType.name: panHipMatchType
panHipMatchType.description: Specifies whether the HIP field represents a HIP Object or a HIP Profile.

panHipRepeatCount.name: panHipRepeatCount
panHipRepeatCount.description: Number of times the HIP profile matched.

panHipOS.name: panHipOS
panHipOS.description: String representing the operating system of the client.
